</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sickmade>Sickmade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/02 6:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.planeteq.com/character/classes/warrior/c_warrior.gif 60 120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blasting through Skyshrine...</span><hr size=1> I am personally just coming off Ally Faction to Kael.  I had maxed Kromzek, Kromriff, and Tormax. (Tormax took the longest)  Kael is really nice faction to be for armor.  There are a few, very few other quests in there that are nice bonuses.  I tried killing dragons and dorfs in order to raise my faction.  I honestly have to say from a warrior point.  Soloing dorfs and wolves it a ton easier than soloing in SS.  Not just because of my level but also because dorfs drop Heads wich can be turned in for faction.  This is MUCH faster than just killing.  <br>
<br>
Once you get a bit of Kael faction, you will want to turn in dorf heads to Capt. Bevelos (sp) inside the bank.  Capt give you all three faction hits plust small coin.  This is nice because its hard to raise Tormax faction.  The recruiter at the EW ent side of Kael will only give Kromriff and Kromzek.  Your strategy of wiping SS pool room might work better, but like I said this is just my first hand experience.<br>
<br>
BTW Kael is not a city with much going on.  Armor turn ins and small quests.  Kael has very little vendors.  No trade skill vendors at all.  This really sucks when it comes to fletching as you will need sombody to go into Thrug and grab your supplies or just TP yourself to a city with supplies.  (I didnt have this option. At the time there was no PoP and Cabilis isn't really in a convienent location.)  Running from EJ to Cabilis everytime I needed somthing got old real fast.  The armor in Kael has insane stats and is well worth the effort.  But on my server.  There was one guild on Kael faction and I wasnt a part of them.  Just now few guilds are begining to switch factions.  Hunting in NToV South Wing (if I remember correctly) is hard to do without a very large guild to back you up.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:navy;font-family:Tahoma;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120240" target="top">Kers - 53 Champion of NGoH</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:navy;font-family:Tahoma;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=201787" target="top">Sickmade - 42 Shaman of NGoH</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
