<br>
Kill in Skyshrine where you said. I had a bot cleric heal me in between fights so she didn't take any faction hits. Just do the circle around there killing non stop. Eventually you'll get dubious to zek (rather quickly). <br>
<br>
Now this is where my strategy differs from others. Most will switch to dwarf heads about this time. I didn't. I want to preserve my coldain factions for the ring and tradeskills. <br>
<br>
So the way I did it was go to velks and duo with the same cleric in the pits. Collect the paws. Lots and lots of them. Last count I had was 600ish paws. I know that seems like a lot, but in a marathon session you can easily get 100. Con some of your sub-60 guildmates into coming there with you. I didn't care about the exp so I got anyone I could to go with me to get them as long as I got all the paws, they could have all the spells/gems/loot that they wanted. More people = less exp, but it also = faster killing, thus more paws.<br>
<br>
You turn the paws in to Capt. Bvellos (same guy you turn heads into).<br>
<br>
Now let me qualify the post:<br>
<br>
This will not be the most efficient way to raise Kromriff. To raise Kromriff with any efficiency, you have to kill dwarves. The paws will raise Zek, Rif and Tormax faction. Zek the fastest, Tormax the next fastest and Rif the slowest. I'm still kos with Rif even after being ally with the other two. So anytime I want to go to Kael, I always have to invis passed the giants near WL zone. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=312137">Sshaithis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> / <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=408738">Meina</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leavandoreq>LeavandorEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/02 9:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blasting through Skyshrine...</span><hr size=1> Grab a cleric or two, or just anyone who can cast any type of AE spell... You don't even need enc stuns anymore, due to the change in how many mobs can attack you.  If you are 60+, you shouldn't worry about your casters getting eaten alive from the agro of AEing.<br>
<br>
Pull about 10-15 mobs at a time, even a single cleric using his two 50+ AEs the mobs die in a little under 20 seconds.<br>
<br>
Pretty fun for a gimp AE group.  Works nice outside of Thurg in GD too. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">_________________</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
