br>
<br>
I got pwned. Hard. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Upon entering ( and my trusty invis dropped as expected ); there's a guardian gargoyle thing ; and around him were about 6 mobs; all which aggroed me as soon as I appeared. I was hit with ice nukes ( wiz ); tashed ( ench ); and with wrath ( cleric ) spells.<br>
<br>
Solo there now is maybe doable once cleared up a little ( respawn rate was around 12 minutes or so if i could remember proper ); but for all intents the normal everyday joe will need help breaking the rotation around the pool in order to keep adds under control ( having the cleric mob add is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>bad</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> solo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . And the enchanter mobs are pretty rough in terms of tashing ya and than all the other critters light you up like a sparkler..<br>
<br>
So I called on the guild; and lo and behold they were already gathering up there. We made it up to almost the quest mob room (old) with 10 people ( mostly 60 )...Drops were decent; exp was good once through the maze; and things progressed along nicely until we came time to log. <br>
<br>
Once near top of the steps before quest mob area (old); there's some new elite drakes who are pretty tough ( flurry, enrage ) hit in the 200's or so...Was quite fun. Biggest problem was CC basically..we tried a few different techniques and some worked for some of the mobs; others were handled differently and it's basically trial and error. Had to do the split tank thing which was handled decently. Reminded me of a simpler ToVW zone in appearance to mob layout and origin points.<br>
<br>
